<th>Route 4</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Monday</td>
<td>22</td>
<td>25</td>
<td>26</td>
<td>26</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Tuesday</td>
<td>26</td>
<td>27</td>
<td>29</td>
<td>28</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Wednesday</td>
<td>25</td>
<td>28</td>
<td>33</td>
<td>27</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Thursday</td>
<td>25</td>
<td>26</td>
<td>30</td>
<td>30</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Friday</td>
<td>31</td>
<td>29</td>
<td>33</td>
<td>30</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<ul>
<li><span>$k = 4$</span></li>
<li><span>$x_{1.} = 129$</span> (total for route 1)</li>
<li><span>$x_{2.} = 135$</span> (total for route 2)</li>
<li><span>$x_{3.} = 151$</span> (total for route 3)</li>
<li><span>$x_{4.} = 141$</span> (total for route 4)</li>
<li><span>$x_{..} = 556$</span> (total for all routes)</li>
<li><span>$n = 5$</span> (number of trial things for each route, all the same)</li>
<li><span>$\sum \sum x_{ij}^2 =15610$</span> (sum of the total-for-each-trip-squared values for all routes)</li>
<li><span>$\sum x_{i.}^2/n_i = 15509.6$</span> (sum of total-for-each-route-squared, divided by 5)</li>
<li><span>$SS(Tr) = 15509.6 - 556^2/20 = 15509.6 - 15456.8 = 52.8$</span> (sum of squares for treatment)</li>
<li><span>$SS(E) = 15610 - 15509.6 = 100.4$</span> (sum of squares for errors)</li>
<li><span>$SS(T) = 52.8 + 100.4 = 153.2$</span> (sum of squares, total)</li>
<li><span>$MS(Tr) = 52.8 / 3 = 17.6$</span></li>
<li><span>$MS(E) = 100.4 / 16 = 6.275$</span></li>
<li><span>$F_{Tr} = 17.6 / 6.275 = 2.804$</span></li>
</ul>
<p>The ANOVA table is:</p>
